1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with fundamental relations between information and estimation in continuous-time channels, which is a core topic in information theory. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper introduces the family of semi-martingale channels, which can be seen as a type of stochastic control system. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses optimal filtering and estimation, which are important topics in machine learning. 
4. cs.ST (Statistics): The paper uses statistical tools such as likelihood ratio sub-martingales and relative entropy. 
5. cs.MS (Mathematical Statistics): The paper presents new representations and results in the context of continuous-time channels, which can be seen as a mathematical statistics problem.
